From: Yuval Mintz <Yuval.Mintz@qlogic.com>
Date: Thu, 27 Mar 2014 13:46:37 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 06/10] bnx2x: Fix possible memory leak on iov error flow
Patch-mainline: v3.15-rc1
Git-commit: dae98cadf743daa480c357b7ba4410423c5f905f
References: bsc#908684 FATE#317539

Commit 2dc33bbc4 "bnx2x: Remove the sriov VFOP mechanism" introduced a possible
memory leak on the error flow during multicast filters configuration.

Reported-by: Dan Carpenter <dan.carpenter@oracle.com>
Signed-off-by: Yuval Mintz <Yuval.Mintz@qlogic.com>
Signed-off-by: Ariel Elior <Ariel.Elior@qlogic.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Cho, Yu-Chen <acho@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2x/bnx2x_sriov.c |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2x/bnx2x_sriov.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2x/bnx2x_sriov.c
@@ -595,6 +595,8 @@ int bnx2x_vf_mcast(struct bnx2x *bp, str
 	rc = bnx2x_config_mcast(bp, &mcast, BNX2X_MCAST_CMD_DEL);
 	if (rc) {
 		BNX2X_ERR("Failed to remove multicasts\n");
+		if (mc)
+			kfree(mc);
 		return rc;
 	}
 
